[0m[49m[39m  150, 173[0m:[39m[49m ### Prerequisites
[0m[49m[39m  151, 174[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  152, 175[0m:[39m[49m | Requirement | Details |
[0m[49m[39m  153, 176[0m:[39m[49m |-------------|---------|
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 154     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon SageMaker, AWS Lambda, Amazon ECS (Fargate), Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon S3, Amazon EventBridge, Amazon CloudWatch |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 155     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `sagemaker:CreateTrainingJob`, `sagemaker:InvokeEndpoint`, `ecs:RunTask`, `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query`, `events:PutRule` |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 156     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **BAA** | Required if case-level data includes PHI (surgeon names linked to patient volumes may qualify) |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 157     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest; ECS: encrypted task storage; all transit over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 158     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Fargate tasks in private subnet with VPC endpoints for S3, DynamoDB, CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 159     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled for audit trail of schedule changes and optimization runs |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 160     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Sample Data** | Synthetic surgical case data. Generate from published OR utilization benchmarks. Never use real patient-linked surgical records in dev. |
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 161     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | SageMaker training: ~$5-20/run (quarterly). Fargate solver: ~$1-10/run (depends on solve time). DynamoDB + Lambda: negligible. Total: $50-200/month including daily reallocation runs. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Services | SageMaker, Lambda, DynamoDB, S3, Step Functions, EventBridge, QuickSight, API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | IAM Permissions | sagemaker:CreateProcessingJob, lambda:InvokeFunction, dynamodb:PutItem/GetItem/Query, s3:GetObject/PutObject, states:StartExecution |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | BAA | Required. Block schedules contain surgeon names and may reference patient case types. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Encryption | S3 SSE-KMS, DynamoDB encryption at rest, TLS in transit |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | VPC | Recommended for SageMaker jobs accessing on-premises EHR data |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | CloudTrail | Audit logging for all optimization runs and allocation changes |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | Sample Data | Synthetic OR case data with realistic duration distributions. Never use real patient data in dev. |
